main event: Multiple reports and correspondence related to UFO sightings at O'Hare Air Force Base from 1957 to 1960.
interesting points: One sighting involved an object hovering over O'Hare AFB for approximately 5 minutes,The opinions of the Air Technical Intelligence Center generally suggested identified aircraft or balloons as explanations,There was a reliable witness who reported an object moving erratically with no visible means of propulsion,One of the photographs submitted was considered unidentifiable and attributed to processing defects,Major L.J. Tacker returned several negatives, indicating they were not suitable for analysis.
